  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Purchase for Progress 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(1)  Build the institutional and commercial capacity of FOs (2) Promote smallholder capacity building (3) To facilitate and promote value addition and access to market information to enable them to access profitable markets. (4) To encourage small scale farmer friendly and gender sensitive marketing models and value chain development approaches.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goal: To link and promote access to viable agricultural markets to increase incomes of smallholder farmers in Gulu, Amuru and Nwoya Districts.
Specific objectives: 
&#x2022; To build the institutional and commercial capacity of FOs to efficiently and effectively manage the SCPs as a marketing hub for small holder farmer produce.
&#x2022; To promote small holder capacity building (managerial, technical, value addition, marketing, post harvest handling) and access to improved inputs (credit, agro-inputs, microfinance, VSLA) through support to FGs.
&#x2022; To facilitate and promote access to input and output market information  through private sector partnerships to enable them to access profitable markets. 
&#x2022; To encourage small scale farmer friendly and gender sensitive marketing models and value chain development approaches.</narrative>
  </description>
